If the Sasakian structure is semi-regular, then $X$ is a smooth K\"ahler manifold. By Proposition 
\ref{prop:locus-orb-K}, the ramification locus consists of smooth K\"ahler curves. We see in Theorem \ref{thm:4g+5}
below that this is not possible.
\end{proof}

